File: Chief Justice Mogoeng Mogoeng. JOHANNESBURG - Chief Justice Mogoeng Mogoeng is appealing a decision for him to retract comments about Israel he made during a webinar in 2020. Mogoeng was found guilty of misconduct by the Judicial Conduct Committee, for his remarks on South Africa's foreign policy on Israel. READ: ACDP protests in support of Chief Justice The chief justice says the findings are flawed and superficial. In the 39-page appeal, he says Judge Phineas Mojapelo failed to deal with constitutional rights to freedom of expression and freedom of religion.